name: Maternity Services
description: West Chester Hospital has been verified as an “Emergency Center of Excellence” by Emergency Excellence, an organization specializing in emergency department benchmarking. As a Level III Trauma Center, and utilizing the same physicians as the University of Cincinnati Medical Center’s Level I Trauma Center, our emergency staff is equipped to address the most emergent and complex medical cases.

name: ECG
description: An electrocardiogram (ECG) is a simple test that can be used to check your hearts rhythm and electrical activity. Sensors attached to the skin are used to detect the electrical signals produced by your heart each time it beats.
